      <h3>Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)</h3>
      <p>Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) can help measure the success of PR campaigns and activities, such as media coverage, website traffic, and engagement rates. Examples of PR KPIs include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Media Impressions: The number of times a media message has been seen or heard by an audience.</li>
        <li>Media Coverage: The number of times an organization has been mentioned in the media.</li>
        <li>Website Traffic: The number of visitors to the organization's website, which can be a measure of the impact of PR efforts on online engagement.</li>
        <li>Engagement Rates: The number of people who interact with a brand's content, such as likes, comments, and shares on social media.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

